# TAMS — Vision Document Guide

Template structure: `docs/templates/vision_template.md`
Output file: `docs/official/vision.md`

Also follow `documentation-standards.mdc`. Preserve all template headings; replace placeholder content with TAMS-specific prose.

## Introduction

State that TAMS is a web-based, microservices-driven platform that enables university teachers to upload student PDF transcripts, automatically parse course data, evaluate graduation eligibility against admin-defined rules, and produce instant reports — without permanently storing PII on disk.

## Positioning

### Problem Statement

Use the template table format:

| The problem of | Manual transcript review against complex, frequently updated graduation requirements |
| affects | University admins, teachers, students, and IT staff |
| the impact of which is | Time-consuming manual checks, inconsistent evaluations, delayed graduation decisions, and privacy risk from mishandled student data |
| a successful solution would be | Automated PDF parsing, rule-based eligibility evaluation, role-based access, and PII-safe processing |

### Product Position Statement

Use the template table format:

| For | University teachers and academic administrators |
| Who | Need to verify student graduation eligibility quickly and consistently |
| The (product name) | TAMS is an academic transcript analysis platform |
| That | Automatically parses PDF transcripts and evaluates them against configurable graduation rules |
| Unlike | Manual spreadsheet-based checks or generic document management tools |
| Our product | Combines domain-specific graduation rule engines with PII-by-design async PDF processing |

## Stakeholder Descriptions

### Stakeholder Summary

| Name | Description | Responsibilities |
|------|-------------|------------------|
| Admin | Academic administrator | Defines and maintains graduation rule sets (departments, courses, categories, equivalence rules); manages users |
| Teacher | Faculty member or advisor | Uploads student transcripts, triggers analysis, views results and history |
| Student | Enrolled student | Views own analysis result (read-only) when linked to a teacher |
| DevOps / IT | Infrastructure operator | Deploys and monitors Docker Compose or Kubernetes environments |
| Development Team | Engineering staff | Builds, tests, and maintains microservices and frontend |

### User Environment

Describe: web browser on desktop (primary); peak usage during graduation periods; standalone MVP with no external SIS integration; React frontend communicating via REST through api-gateway; three user roles (ADMIN, TEACHER, STUDENT).

## Product Overview

### Needs and Features

Table columns: **Need | Priority | Features | Planned Release**

Include at minimum:

| Need | Priority | Features | Planned Release |
|------|----------|----------|-----------------|
| Secure access | Must | JWT auth, role-based routing, mandatory password change | MVP |
| Rule management | Must | Department, course, graduation category, curriculum equivalence CRUD | MVP |
| Transcript analysis | Must | PDF upload, async Kafka parsing, graduation engine, result display | MVP |
| PII protection | Must | In-memory PDF processing, PII masking, short Kafka retention | MVP |
| Operational readiness | Should | Health checks, Docker Compose and K8s deployment, HTTPS support | MVP |

Verify feature status against `docs/todo.md` before marking as delivered.

